<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Transitional//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-transitional.dtd">
<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" xml:lang="en" lang="en">
<head>
  <title></title>
  <meta http-equiv="content-type" content="text/html; charset=utf-8" />
  <link href="/stylesheets/scriptaculous.css" media="screen" rel="Stylesheet" type="text/css" />
  <script src="/javascripts/prototype.js" type="text/javascript"></script>
  <script src="/javascripts/effects.js" type="text/javascript"></script>
  <script src="/javascripts/dragdrop.js" type="text/javascript"></script>
  <script src="/javascripts/controls.js" type="text/javascript"></script>
</head>
<body>
  <div id="content">
    <h1>Meal Planning</h1>

<p>Define meals by using the Add link.  <br />
Select an existing meal in the third column to edit it or choose 'Add Meal Menu' to work on a blank one.</p>
<p><b>AutoSave:  </b>
Adding a recipe to a meal or deleting it from a meal is automatically saved in the background, hence there is no save button. </p> 
  
<a href="#" onclick="alert(single_meal_menu_id);">Show me the value of single_meal_menu_id!</a>

<h2>Available meal menus:</h2>
<table>
<tr style="vertical-align: top;">
  <td style="width: 20%; vertical-align: top;">
   <h2>Recipe Search Form</h2>
   <div id="recipe_search_form_div">
     <%= render_partial 'recipe_search_form' %>
   </div>
   <div id="matching_recipes_div">
     <h2>Recipe Search Results</h2>
     <% # render :partial => 'recipe_search_results' %>
     <div id="recipe_search_results">
     </div>
   </div>
  </td>
  <td style="width: 50%; vertical-align: top;">
   <div id="meal_container_div">
     <h2>Active Meal</h2>
     <div id="meal_div">
       <script type="text/javascript"> single_meal_menu_id = -1;</script>
       Click *Add Meal Menu* to the right to prepare a blank meal menu.
       <% # render :partial => 'show_single_meal' %>
     </div>
   </div>
  </td>
  <td style="width: 30%; vertical-align: top;">
   <div id="meal_list_div">
     <%= render :partial => 'list_all_meals' %>
   </div>
  </td>
</tr> 
</table>

</body></html>
